<details open="open"><summary class="section-head">History</summary>

<blockquote>
	<h3>Early Life</h3>
	Born into the Sparrow family on the rugged, storm-laden Island of Vervarda, Alys was born to, Sparrow D. Jack, a steadfast Marine Vice Admiral, and Varentos Alista owner of The Varentos Tavern. Due to her grandmother being, the legendary Marine Admiral Sparrow D. Hina, Alys' early years were shaped with a relentless dedication to the Marine cause. From a young age, her life was forged in rigorous training, every lesson preparing her to carry forward her family’s legacy and uphold the Sparrow name within the ranks of the Marines.<br><br>
	
	When Alys was old enough, she enlisted in the Marines and swiftly earned her place among their ranks. Her skill and determination were unmatched, and by just 18, she had risen to the esteemed rank of Captain, a feat rarely achieved by one so young. For a year, she commanded with strength and resolve—until tragedy struck. Her home town was destroyed and her mother was brutally murdered by pirates, who seized upon the absence of Marines after they were summoned from Vervarda to join a critical Buster Call. This loss etched a deep scar in Alys’s heart, fueling a new fire within her that would drive her journey forward.<br><br>

	<h3>Defection & Found Family</h3>
	Disillusioned by the Marine's betrayal and seeking her own path, Alys broke free from their ranks, setting sail to carve out her destiny. Her journey took a thrilling turn when she discovered the fabled Inu Inu no Mi: Model Raiju, a Devil Fruit of ancient, storm-forged power. Without hesitation, she ate it, harnessing the electric fury of the mythical Raiju. Shortly after, fate brought her to Whitebeard himself. Days of conversation with the legendary captain unveiled a kindred spirit, and Alys chose to join his crew, setting her course as a pirate.<br><br>

Over the next five years, Alys rose to prominence among the Whitebeard Pirates, who had become her true family. Her strength and loyalty earned her the revered title of Division Commander, and the world came to know her as the "Divine Tempest." With a bounty of 2,143,000,000 Berries on her head, she was a force to be reckoned with. But in her sixth year with Whitebeard’s crew, tragedy struck. Blackbeard’s betrayal led to the capture of Ace, who's execution was quickly organised at Marineford. The ensuing battle ended up claiming both Ace’s life and that of Whitebeard himself, leaving Alys with a heavy heart and a burning desire for vengance against Blackbeard & The Marines.<br><br>

	<h3>Post Paramount War - Present</h3>
	In the two turbulent years following the Paramount War, Alys gathered a powerful crew—the Sparrow Pirates—whom she treated as her own kin. Fueled by vengeance and ambition, she launched ruthless assaults on Marine convoys, struck fear into the hearts of World Nobles, and tirelessly hunted the infamous Blackbeard. Her relentless rise culminated in an epic showdown against Argon Xilentino, one of the Five Emperors of the Sea. After defeating and killing him in combat, she seized his territories and took his place among the Emperors of the Sea for herself.<br><br>

Her constant raids and her terrifying mastery of the Awakened Raiju Devil Fruit made her a nightmare for the World Government, who recognized her as a grave threat to world stability. Alys's position as an Emperor and her insurrectionary crusade led them to increase her bounty to the staggering amount of 5,285,000,000 Berries, branding her as one of the world’s most dangerous and untameable figures and granting her the second highest bounty ever issued.
</blockquote>

